title: Honey-Soy-Glazed Salmon With Peppers
subtitle: Need a new way to enjoy an old favorite? This honey-soy glazed salmon is delectable
description: Heat oven to 475 degrees F. Stir together 3 tablespoons vinegar, 1 tablespoon sesame oil, soy sauce, and next 3 ingredients; set aside 1/2 cup of sauce. Place salmon, skin side down, on a large parchment lined rimmed baking sheet. Brush with 2 tablespoons soy mixture.
